A third-person survival game built with Unreal Engine 4.  
Features:
- AI zombies
- Companion AI bot
- Inventory & shooting systems

Today, artificial intelligence is transforming various fields of modern 
technology, including the gaming industry. Gaming has become one of 
the largest entertainment sectors, following movies and music, and is 
widely consumed by people of all ages. While games range from simple 
to highly complex, individuals with disabilities often face challenges in 
playing competitive or intricate games. Additionally, traditional game 
controls can limit the ability of players to issue real-time commands 
efficiently. 
In this paper, we present the integration of artificial intelligence and 
gaming to enhance the overall player experience. Our approach enables 
AI-assisted gameplay and voice-controlled interactions, allowing disabled 
players to engage in competitive gaming on equal terms. By combining 
AI voice recognition with character control, we introduce an accessible 
and immersive gaming experience that improves interaction and 
inclusivity for all players.

This project was developed to bridge that gap, creating a high-quality 
competitive 3D game that mirrors the excitement and complexity of 
famous action games while incorporating AI-driven voice recognition to 
enhance both strategy and accessibility.  that is both thrilling for regular 
players and fully accessible to individuals who cannot use traditional 
controllers.

1. Players can control their character using voice commands instead 
of traditional controllers and issue orders to bot. 
2. Fast-paced and skill-based mechanics similar to popular 
competitive shooter games. 
3. Designed for both traditional gamers and people with disabilities. 
4. AI-controlled enemies react intelligently to player actions. 
5. Realistic Shooting and Combat System. 
6. High-quality 3D environments with realistic textures and lighting. 
7. Intuitive UI design for easy navigation and accessibility. 


